# Adding New Feature Coverage

When adding a new feature module (e.g., "05-interviews"), follow this checklist:

## Step 1: Create Test Data

Create `src/data/<feature>.data.json` with the input data the tests will use:
```json
{
  "validScenario": {
    "field1": "value1",
    "field2": "value2"
  }
}
```

## Step 2: Create Page Object

Create `src/page-objects/<NN>-<feature>/<feature>.page.ts`:

```typescript
import { expect } from "@playwright/test";
import { BasePage } from "../00-shared/base.page";

export interface FeatureData {
  field1: string;
  field2: string;
}

export class FeaturePage extends BasePage {
  // Locators as readonly class fields
  private readonly formCard = this.page.getByTestId("card-feature-form");
  readonly sectionTitle = this.page.getByRole("heading", { name: /Feature/i });

  async goto(): Promise<void> {
    await this.navigateTo("/feature-route");
    await this.page.waitForLoadState("domcontentloaded");
  }

  async verifyPageLoaded(): Promise<void> {
    await expect(this.sectionTitle).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15000 });
  }

  // ... fill, submit, verify methods
}
```

## Step 3: Register in Barrel Export

Add to `src/page-objects/index.ts`:
```typescript
export { FeaturePage } from "./<NN>-<feature>/<feature>.page";
export type { FeatureData } from "./<NN>-<feature>/<feature>.page";
```

## Step 4: Register Fixture

Update `src/fixtures/test.fixture.ts`:

```typescript
import { FeaturePage } from "../page-objects/<NN>-<feature>/<feature>.page";

export const test = base.extend<{
  // existing fixtures...
  featurePage: FeaturePage;
}>({
  // existing fixtures...
  featurePage: async ({ page }, use) => {
    await use(new FeaturePage(page));
  },
});
```

## Step 5: Create Test Spec

Create `tests/<NN>-<feature>.spec.ts`:
```typescript
import { test, expect } from "../src/fixtures/test.fixture";
import featureData from "../src/data/<feature>.data.json";
import type { FeatureData } from "../src/page-objects/<NN>-<feature>/<feature>.page";

test.describe("Feature Name - Test Suite", () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ featurePage }) => {
    await featurePage.goto();
    await featurePage.verifyPageLoaded();
  });

  test("TC_<MODULE>_01: Description", async ({ featurePage }) => {
    // ...
  });
});
```

## Step 6: Add NPM Scripts

Update `package.json` scripts:
```json
{
  "test:<feature>": "npx playwright test tests/<NN>-<feature>.spec.ts",
  "test:ci:<feature>": "CI=true npx playwright test tests/<NN>-<feature>.spec.ts"
}
```

## Step 7: Update Jenkinsfile

Add the new suite to the `getTestCommand()` switch and the `TEST_SUITE` parameter choices:
```groovy
parameters {
  choice(name: 'TEST_SUITE', choices: ['all', 'login', 'dashboard', 'requisition', 'referrals', '<feature>'], ...)
}

def getTestCommand(String suite) {
  switch (suite) {
    case '<feature>':
      return 'npx playwright test tests/<NN>-<feature>.spec.ts --reporter=list,html,junit,./src/reporters/custom-dashboard.reporter.ts'
    // ...
  }
}
```
